If you would like to contribute or have any question, please don't hesitate to contact me. ## Organizations The library was created and open-sourced by Shuyue Jia @ Human Sensor Laboratory, School of Automation Engineering, and the School of Computer Science, Northeast Electric Power University, Jilin, China.
info.name: eeg-dl
info.summary: A Deep Learning library for EEG Signals Classification
info.html_description:
Welcome to EEG Deep Learning Library

EEG-DL is a Deep Learning (DL) library written by TensorFlow for EEG Tasks (Signals) Classification. It provides the latest DL algorithms and keeps updated.

Documentation

The supported models include

No. Model Example
1 Deep Neural Networks DNN
2 Convolutional Neural Networks [Tutorial] CNN
3 Deep Residual Convolutional Neural Networks ResNet CNN
4 Densely Connected Convolutional Neural Networks DenseNet CNN
5 Fully Convolutional Neural Networks Fully Conv CNN
6 Graph Convolutional Neural Networks [Tutorial] GCN / Graph CNN
7 Deep Residual Graph Convolutional Neural Networks ResGCN
8 Densely Connected Graph Convolutional Neural Networks Dense GCN
9 Recurrent Neural Networks RNN
10 Attention-based Recurrent Neural Networks RNN with Attention
11 Bidirectional Recurrent Neural Networks BiRNN
12 Attention-based Bidirectional Recurrent Neural Networks BiRNN with Attention
13 Long-short Term Memory LSTM
14 Attention-based Long-short Term Memory LSTM with Attention
15 Bidirectional Long-short Term Memory BiLSTM
16 Attention-based Bidirectional Long-short Term Memory BiLSTM with Attention
17 Gated Recurrent Unit GRU
18 Attention-based Gated Recurrent Unit GRU with Attention
19 Bidirectional Gated Recurrent Unit BiGRU
20 Attention-based Bidirectional Gated Recurrent Unit BiGRU with Attention

Two EEG Motor Imagery (MI) benchmarks are currently provided. Other benchmarks in the field of EEG can be found here.

No. Dataset
1 EEG Motor Movement/Imagery Dataset [Access]
2 High Gamma Dataset [Access]

The evaluation criteria consists of

Evaluation Metrics [Tutorial]
Accuracy / Precision / Recall / F1 Score / Kappa Coefficient
Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve / Area under the Curve (AUC)
Confusion Matrix
Paired-wise t-test (via R language [Tutorial])

Installation

EEG-DL Library is still under development. Before the first stable release (1.0), please clone the repository and run

pip install .

in the main directory. This will install EEG-DL Library and its dependencies automatically. EEG-DL Library also requires TensorFlow 1.13.0 or later. Because users should choose whether to install the cpu or gpu version of TensorFlow, we do not include it in the dependencies. We highly recommend to train models under GPU devices since they're faster. See Installing TensorFlow.

Citation

If you find our library useful, please considering citing our paper in your publications. We provide a BibTeX entry below.

@article{hou2019novel,  
 year = 2020,  
 month = {feb},  
 publisher = {IOP Publishing},  
 volume = {17},  
 number = {1},  
 pages = {016048},  
 author = {Yimin Hou and Lu Zhou and Shuyue Jia and Xiangmin Lun},  
 title = {A novel approach of decoding {EEG} four-class motor imagery tasks via scout {ESI} and {CNN}},  
 journal = {Journal of Neural Engineering}  
}

Contribution

We always welcome contributions to help make EEG-DL Library better. If you would like to contribute or have any question, please don't hesitate to contact me.

Organizations

The library was created and open-sourced by Shuyue Jia @ Human Sensor Laboratory, School of Automation Engineering, and the School of Computer Science, Northeast Electric Power University, Jilin, China.
